---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Elizabeth Armstrong Therapy" description="Meet Elizabeth Armstrong, LMFT. A narrative therapist in Orange County offering collaborative, warm therapy for individuals, couples, and families.">

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">About Me</p>
      <h1>Hello, I'm Elizabeth</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I'm a licensed marriage and family therapist who believes that you already have what you need to live the life you want. My job is to help you find it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About Intro Section -->
  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-intro">
        <div class="about-image-wrapper">
          <div class="about-image-placeholder">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1">
              <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/>
              <circle cx="8.5" cy="8.5" r="1.5"/>
              <path d="M21 15l-5-5L5 21"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="about-image-decoration"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-text">
          <h2>Why I became a therapist</h2>
          <p>
            I've always been fascinated by stories: the ones we inherit from our families, the ones we tell ourselves, and the ones we're still writing. I came to therapy because I wanted to help people discover that they have more authorship over their lives than they might realize.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before becoming a therapist, I spent years in roles where I learned to listen deeply and hold space for complexity. That experience taught me that people don't need to be fixed. They need to be heard, respected, and gently invited to see themselves and their situations from new angles.
          </p>
          <p>
            I believe therapy should feel like a partnership. You bring your expertise about your own life; I bring curiosity, warmth, and a set of tools we can explore together. There's no script, no judgment, and no pretending to have all the answers. Just two people working together to understand what's happening and what's possible.
          </p>

          <div class="decorative-line"></div>

          <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--text-secondary);">
            "I don't see my role as telling you who to be. I see it as helping you reconnect with who you already are, and supporting you as you step more fully into that."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to Expect Section -->
  <section class="section bg-blush">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow text-center">Working Together</p>
      <h2 class="text-center">What to expect in sessions</h2>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">
        <p>
          When we work together, you can expect a space that's warm, genuine, and free of judgment. I won't rush you or push you anywhere you're not ready to go. At the same time, I won't let you stay stuck if we can help it.
        </p>

        <p>
          Sessions are typically conversational. We might explore a specific situation that's been on your mind, trace patterns that keep showing up in your life, or slow down to examine what certain experiences have meant to you. Sometimes we'll work with specific techniques; other times we'll simply talk and reflect.
        </p>

        <p>
          I tend to ask a lot of questions, not because I'm testing you, but because I'm genuinely curious. I want to understand what matters to you, what you've been through, and what kind of life you're hoping to build. Your answers guide where we go.
        </p>

        <p>
          Above all, you can expect to be treated as a whole person, not a set of symptoms. I'm interested in your strengths, your values, your moments of joy, not just your struggles. We'll work with all of it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- My Style Section -->
  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow text-center">My Therapeutic Style</p>
      <h2 class="text-center">How I work</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top: var(--space-10); gap: var(--space-6);">
        <div style="text-align: center; padding: var(--space-6);">
          <svg style="width: 48px; height: 48px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-4); color: var(--sage);" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/>
            <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/>
            <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/>
            <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/>
          </svg>
          <h4>Collaborative</h4>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-secondary);">
            We're partners in this work. I bring my training and perspective; you bring your lived experience and wisdom about your own life.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="text-align: center; padding: var(--space-6);">
          <svg style="width: 48px; height: 48px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-4); color: var(--sage);" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/>
          </svg>
          <h4>Reflective</h4>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-secondary);">
            I help you slow down and look at things from different angles. Sometimes the most powerful work happens when we pause to notice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="text-align: center; padding: var(--space-6);">
          <svg style="width: 48px; height: 48px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-4); color: var(--sage);" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M21 15a2 2 0 01-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2z"/>
          </svg>
          <h4>Interactive</h4>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-secondary);">
            Therapy isn't passive. I'll ask questions, offer observations, and engage actively in our conversation. We think together.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-12); padding: var(--space-8); background: var(--bg-secondary); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">What I draw from</h4>
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-secondary);">
          My work is grounded in <strong>narrative therapy</strong>, which focuses on the stories we tell about ourselves and our lives, and how those stories shape our experience. I also draw from <strong>collaborative therapy</strong>, <strong>systemic approaches</strong>, and <strong>attachment theory</strong>. I believe in meeting each person where they are and adapting my approach to what's most helpful for you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Credentials Section -->
  <section class="section bg-sand">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow text-center">Education & Training</p>
      <h2 class="text-center">Credentials</h2>

      <div class="credentials-list" style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">
        <div class="credential-item">
          <div class="credential-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;">
              <path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/>
              <path d="M6 12v5c0 1.5 3 3 6 3s6-1.5 6-3v-5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-content">
            <h4>Master of Arts in Marriage & Family Therapy</h4>
            <p>University of California, Placeholder Campus</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="credential-item">
          <div class="credential-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;">
              <rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="16" rx="2"/>
              <path d="M7 8h10M7 12h6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-content">
            <h4>Licensed Marriage & Family Therapist (LMFT)</h4>
            <p>California Board of Behavioral Sciences, License #111154</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="credential-item">
          <div class="credential-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;">
              <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/>
              <path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/>
              <path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-content">
            <h4>Advanced Training in Narrative Therapy</h4>
            <p>Dulwich Centre, Adelaide, Australia</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="credential-item">
          <div class="credential-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <path d="M8 12l3 3 5-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-content">
            <h4>Gottman Method Couples Therapy, Level 1</h4>
            <p>The Gottman Institute</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Personal Note Section -->
  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container container-text">
      <h2 class="text-center">A little more about me</h2>
      <div class="decorative-line center"></div>

      <p>
        Outside of the therapy room, you'll find me walking by the ocean, reading novels I probably should have read years ago, and attempting to keep houseplants alive with varying degrees of success. I believe in slowing down, in the power of a good conversation, and in the quiet moments where we actually hear ourselves think.
      </p>

      <p>
        I know that reaching out to a therapist takes courage. Whether you're ready to schedule a consultation or just browsing to see if this might be a fit, I'm glad you're here.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Band -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Let's see if we're a good fit</h2>
      <p>
        I offer a free 15-minute consultation where we can talk about what you're looking for and whether I might be the right therapist for you.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact.html" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Schedule Your Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
